t gift but an elixir of the human spirit.', 11327, 0), (172619, 'Life does not happen to you, it happens for you. Savor every flavor.', 11327, 0), (172620, 'Savor life authentically.', 11327, 0), (172621, 'Learn from the past, but don''t live there, Plan the future, but don’t live there. Remember the Present is where we truly spend the rest of our lives.', 11327, 0), (172622, 'Honoring what you deserve is the beginning of living.', 11327, 0), (172623, 'How a person looks at life is a pristine example of how that person is going to live life.', 11327, 0), (172624, 'Life has been fair, destiny may have staged it well but the timings were terrible.', 6344, 0), (172625, 'It''s not about who you used to be, it''s about who you have become.', 11327, 0), (172626, 'I am what I am and I can''t change it. I know how to cope and how to get by. I don''t want or expect anyone to stand with me. I don''t need anyone to. I''ve learned to accept my life just the way it is, and I don''t give a damn if you or anyone else doesn''t.', 466, 0), (172627, 'used to see people in love . seeing them ,used to say -how heavenly it is ,they looks so happy in love. now i touched by love- and don''t say the same .', 6237, 0), (172628, 'Sadly, some folks don’t live . . . they merely exist.', 6413, 0), (172629, 'This is what I call life: a God to save, a woman to love, a job to do, and a cause to fight', 31894, 0), (172630, 'The picture enclosed here is of a hibiscus that has been flowering in the parlor window one bloom at a time for what seems like a year or more. It’s getting to where I don’t remember when there wasn’t a bud or two and a flower either out or on the way.This morning there is a fresh new flower just like the one in the picture, but right next to it is the one that was new yesterday and is already spent. I don’t know whether to be happy for the beautiful one or sad for the one that is gone. I guess if I wait until tomorrow I can be sad for the one that is so beautiful now. But how can I anticipate being sad for something that is so pretty?It’s really a good thing that people can only “see” the present because we are on the same train as a hibiscus except that we are on a longer trip. I’ve told you before but it fits in here so I will say it again. Sometimes I get feeling so good that I get afraid to anticipate the loss. If life could be a series of beautiful scenes and beautiful music and pleasant visits with people we love, then life should just go on forever. I suppose that’s why people get old and feeble with wandering minds. What is can end without too much loss, and what was did not stop so will be forever. Right now and as far as I can see, I want to be this morning’s flower. I’ll be a hibiscus. You be a rose…', 12607, 0), (172631, 'Anais Nin responds to the age-old question of why some people are compelled to write:We... write to heighten our own awareness of life, we write to lure and enchant and console others, we write to serenade our lovers. We write to taste life twice, in the moment and in retrospection. We write, like Proust, to render all of it eternal, and to persuade ourselves that it is eternal. We write to be able to transcend our life, to reach beyond it. We write to teach ourselves to speak with others, to record the journey into the labyrinth, we write to expand our world when we feel strangled, or constricted, or lonely. We write as the birds sing. As the primitive dance their rituals. If you do not breathe through writing, if you do not cry out in writing, or sing in writing, then don’t write.Now, please read that one more time. But this time, substitute the word “live” for the word “write” and there you have it—the point that’s always been right there in front of our nose.', 31895, 0), (172632, 'Nurture Nature and Nature will Nurture you.', 5507, 0), (172633, 'Together we can;alone I can''t".', 5489, 0), (172634, 'At any specific stage of your life, you are certain about few things which when passes over the time to be something uncertain and vice versa.', 12339, 0), (172635, 'Life is something which can''t be defined, but can only be celebrated.', 31896, 0), (172636, 'Feminine way of life is "life by probabilities". There are no absolutes, and the same laws can be interpreted differently at different times. Change is the only constant, and people live by Passion, Beauty and Freedom. But with too much freedom it can decline into decadence, corruption and debauchery.', 479, 0), (172637, 'Life is a journey filled with lessons, hardships, heartaches, joys, celebrations and special moments that will ultimately lead us to our destination, our purpose in life. The road will not always be smooth; in fact, throughout our travels, we will encounter many challenges.Some of these challenges will test our courage, strengths, weaknesses, and faith. Along the way, we may stumble upon obstacles that will come between the paths that we are destined to take. In order to follow the right path, we must overcome these obstacles. Sometimes these obstacles are really blessings in disguise, only we don''t realize that at the time.', 12653, 0), (172638, 'You needn''t be afraid of life! Life is so good when you do something that is good and just.', 57, 0), (172639, 'Hope for the best and Prepare for the Worst.', 31897, 0), (172640, 'When old age knocks, even a mighty lion resort to eating frogs.', 31898, 0), (172641, 'The truth is that no one is truthful these days!', 12721, 0), (172642, 'Sometimes we have to think of the worst so we can figure out how to pick up the pieces and move on. Don''t let life slap you with a cold shock', 31899, 0), (172643, 'The only way to live life is to live in the present. You can''t put things off thinking you''ll have time later. There may not be a later. - Katarina Kozlov', 6580, 0), (172644, 'I embrace, I veritably hug and cuddle, the concept of optimism. It is the core of my approach to my existence.', 12624, 0), (172645, 'The world we know is dwarfed by the worlds we don''t. Why not explore them all? Being out there in the wilderness, you have no idea what''ll happen, really. It could be just you and this gorgeous night sky, or maybe you are surfing and some big ass wave comes at you, and if you don''t ride that sucker, it''ll put you under and have you for lunch, or you might turn a corner on a hike and there''s some beautiful deer and her little fawn-- now that has meaning, all of those things, and I need more of that and less of trying to make money so I can pay bills to live in a way I just don''t care about anymore.', 31900, 0), (172646, 'But maybe no one knew that much. Maybe everyone was making it up as they went along, the same as me.', 11643, 0), (172647, 'Never say never because limits, like fears, are often illusions.', 12105, 0), (172648, 'Love Life, Life is Beautiful.', 31901, 0), (172649, 'Trust is all about instinct. If you had all the facts, you wouldn''t need trust. Trust is what is required in the absence of proof. But I believe you can strengthen your instincts by testing them; every time you prove yourself right or wrong, they grow stronger.', 4426, 0), (172650, 'The demons you need to get rid of are inside. But they seem out there because you left the window open.', 9382, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (172651, 'Life is like playing musical chairs –– you never know when the music will stop.” ~', 6413, 0), (172652, 'Nothing''s ever simple. I just don''t want you to ignore possibilities out of fear. Sometimes you have to take a leap of faith, believing that somebody''s going to catch you.', 31902, 0), (172653, 'Sometimes being oblivious is a blessing.', 31903, 0), (172654, 'That which didn''t kill them made them stranger.', 14192, 0), (172655, 'What better time to try something new than when you have nothing to lose.', 12680, 0), (172656, 'It’s better to make baby steps in the right direction than big steps in the wrong direction!', 7682, 0), (172657, 'There''s nothing like a good, long sleep to allow unpleasantness to recede into the past.', 22138, 0), (172658, 'The fear of death never left me; I couldn''t get used to the thought; I would still sometimes shake and weep with terror. By contrast, the fact of existence here and now sometimes took on a glorious splendour.', 477, 0), (172659, 'Once in life always in heart', 31904, 0), (172660, 'If Money Is Everything Then We Mean Nothing', 18017, 0), (172661, 'In Buddhism we also interprete Dharma to mean ''cessation,'' as in the end of dissatisfaction, the end of dukkha. This is the purpose of Buddha''s teachings.', 22138, 0), (172662, 'Revenge is an ugly thing. "He who seeks revenge digs two graves" I only say this because there are circumstances of life where JUSTICE IS NOT ENOUGH OR JUSTICE CAN''T BE HANDED DOWN. Those circumstances require to be AVENGED. This is when you MUST INFLICT PENALTY OR PUNISHMENT for that pain or harm done to you or another. To avenge a wrong is to seek vengeance or revenge. To make right that which was done wrong especially if that wrong caused grievous harm to you or another. This is a situation where vengeance or to avenge or to seek revenge is RIGHT AND JUST!. My explanation also should put some clarity on the old saying "Revenge is a dish best served COLD!', 5162, 0), (172663, 'Sorry’ is, indeed, one of the most difficult and most powerful words in the English language, provided one can feel and say it at the same time.', 12159, 0), (172664, 'While some people want to be popular, some of us simply want to be brave.', 5137, 0), (172665, 'when at times to remind us of the blessings we have been giventhen we are more likely to understand how special our lives areit''s not by chance as some would maybe believebut the grand design of love and fulfillment,...', 20483, 0), (172666, 'You''re the guy who tried to get my cab. I knew I knew you! You scared the bejesus out of me. Come to think of it it was easy to get a cab during rush hour? I am sorry. I had no idea it was your cab. Let me make it up to you. How about a nice hot dog and a beer.Just a hot dog then.Some coffee?Milk?Soda?Tea?LifeSavers?Slurpee?Just let me know. I''m here. I knew I knew ya!', 31905, 0), (172667, 'Life will have less drama if you keep your circle small. You don’t have to be friends with anyone. Pick people who will influence you. Pick the people who share the same interests and radiate the positivity that you have.', 12701, 0), (172668, 'The end is the matter! A step to the end is a factor!', 4606, 0), (172669, 'Sometimes all you need in your life is anything strange because strange things can revive your soul just like a cold water freshening your pale face with every splash!', 3701, 0), (172670, 'You''re the guy who tried to get my cab. I knew I knew you! You scared the bejesus out of me. Come to think of it it was easy to get a cab during rush hour? I am sorry. I had no idea it was your cab. Let me make it up to you. How about a nice hot dog and a beer.Just a hot dog then.Some coffee?Milk?Soda?Tea?LifeSavers?Slurpee?Just let me know. I''m here. knew I knew ya!', 31905, 0), (172671, 'Another thought hits me hard as a lawn dart to the eye: this moment is so terribly unimportant to the rest of the world, yet it means everything to me somehow - and it''s enough.So I sign and I sign and I sign.', 607, 0), (172672, 'Life is biting into a cupcake and finding an eyeball at its center.', 31906, 0), (172673, 'But for anything to be alive, it required motion : the current must run, the record must turn, a person must leave or find another path. Without movement or change, the world became nothing more than a stale copy, and this was the trouble with Ba''s elegant calligraphy, his patient life, it was frozen in time.', 3115, 0), (172674, 'Death is the price you paid for being born.', 5883, 0), (172675, 'Any silly ism or stupid book that considers men above women, must be shunned like a lowlife demon. For, all''s one, barring none.', 4618, 0), (172676, 'In a company of children and grown-ups, the latter are those who should demonstrate good manners and always let the children speak first.', 22378, 0), (172677, 'Life''s like a book: What matters is the hook. Be it short or long, just live it strong. Whether it''s five stars, or how near or far, just soar!', 5065, 0), (172678, 'She wanted to read and talk and laugh and watch television and listen to the radio. She wanted to watch the world around her go by, and make up stories in her head about everything she saw...Like a princess in a carriage, surveying her kingdom, preferably one with a magical forest.', 12920, 0), (172679, 'We''re living in a world which gives us no chance to live".', 31907, 0), (172680, 'Life is unfair, but that''s no reason to give up on it', 33, 0), (172681, 'Forgiving yourself is the first step, forgetting, well it never goes away. Moving forward and walking with one foot in front of the other does get you somewhere. Just keep walking.', 15338, 0), (172682, 'Your promise is someone''s hope. Keep your promises.', 11388, 0), (172683, 'If we don''t cherish those who stay near, what do we have? Only longing.', 31908, 0), (172684, 'Jöns: But feel, to the very end, the triumph of being alive!', 3396, 0), (172685, 'Instead of lullabies, my mother would sing us songs of the Revolution. Now she sings them to her grandchildren. ''Are you nuts?'' I ask her. She replies, ''I don''t know any other songs.', 7813, 0), (172686, 'Struggle is like a Tunnel in the road of Life. You have to enter, you have to come out.', 12400, 0), (172687, 'Ties are straightened and expressions banished.', 7994, 0), (172688, 'Oh my God, what if you wake up some day, and you’re 65, or 75, and you never got your memoir or novel written; or you didn’t go swimming in warm pools and oceans all those years because your thighs were jiggly and you had a nice big comfortable tummy; or you were just so strung out on perfectionism and people-pleasing that you forgot to have a big juicy creative life, of imagination and radical silliness and staring off into space like when you were a kid? It’s going to break your heart. Don’t let this happen.', 457, 0), (172689, 'Don’t complain against life, it may hear you and double your suffering', 3682, 0), (172690, 'You will never really think hard about your life until your oxygen mask is taken away from you when you are at the bed of the ocean. At that exact moment, your true self will be revealed. You will really know if you are a believer or an atheist, whether you really love life or hate it as you usually say. All your claims will be tested', 3682, 0), (172691, 'Sometimes a bit of compassion and decency is reason enough to do something out of the ordinary.', 31909, 0), (172692, 'We don''t know where we come from and where we go, we fill the missing links with whatever our imaginations can provide us', 3682, 0), (172693, 'Then nothing became something, and I was born, and I wrought great havoc in the world in the time allotted to me, and I returned to nothingness', 3682, 0), (172694, 'What if you wake up some day, and you’re 65… and you were just so strung out on perfectionism and people-pleasing that you forgot to have a big juicy creative life?', 457, 0), (172695, 'The real beauty is living life to it''s fullest, to reach a destination and live life for the Lord.', 15338, 0), (172696, 'Numquam illegitimi carborundum --"Never let the bastards grind you down.”-- my old Latin prof Dr. Kuk''''s version, other minor variations out there.', 31910, 0), (172697, 'I''d like to go with you, but I wanna stay home with you', 12646, 0), (172698, 'In this life, you can not understand what you do have not lived.', 31911, 0), (172699, 'numquam illegitimi carborundum --"Never let the bastards grind you down.', 31912, 0), (172700, 'Desire is to ask for something in silence, without really wanting it, for having it wouldn''t fill you as much as having desired it.', 31913, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (172701, 'There is a lot of unhappiness in this world. Try not to feed it.', 5027, 0), (172702, 'A good human being can still be molded from bad clay', 5162, 0), (172703, 'Innovation needs preparation, collaboration and the light of the soul. Every challenge provides that light - a greater depth of understanding about life and truth.', 379, 0), (172704, 'Take heart. You''re not alone. Every broken heart breathes again. That''s life. It goes on. In loss, and in gain.', 4618, 0), (172705, 'Maybe there is an invisible world working behind our own, maybe words in the silence, maybe movements in what looks completely still. When every door is closed, maybe doors are opening that can’t be seen.', 8757, 0), (172706, 'Water in, water out until there is no water to run and the riverbed runs dry. That''s life', 3682, 0), (172707, 'Life has no map; it''s made of random events, always caused by something beyond your control.', 3682, 0), (172708, 'We are revolutionaries for peace and freedom not violence. And we are going to fight through creativity rather than aggression.', 5521, 0), (172709, 'Life is just a dream, to some it''s a sweet dream, to others, a nightmare. But whatever it is, it''s always short and dissipates quickly.', 3682, 0), (172710, 'We live like sheep in line waiting to be slaughtered in a slaughterhouse. We eat and laugh and fight as we see those in front of us fall to the knife', 3682, 0), (172711, 'A small event as tiny as a drop of a pin can change the direction of your entire life', 3682, 0), (172712, 'Let''s Play Cat & MouseIt was a beautiful day as he walked the streets,filled with flowers of summer and the green of the trees.The sun just rising, the freshness in the air.In the distance, something rolled across the road,pushed and played with by a fluffy, tiger like cat.It rolled, and was poked and pushed to the edge …Stop that, Stop that, Stop that now …it’s tiny little legs on the floor as it stretched as tall as it could,arms in front, as it looked up at fluffy …No, No, NoYou can’t catch me …Shocked and amazed was fluffy …As his morning breakfast, scurried and hurried along the side of the road …Goodbye, Good Day, have a wonderful Day …As they continued their day …No more time for Let’s play cat and mouse.by Natasha Parker Copyright © 2014 by Luisa Natasha Parker', 8920, 0), (172713, 'Learn to accept life in toto. A perfect life is only in the dream world. This, my dear, with all it''s heartaches, is it. Our world.', 4618, 0), (172714, 'Oh, let us love our occupations,Bless the squire and his relations,Live upon our daily rations,And always know our proper stations.', 96, 0), (172715, 'Words don''t means', 31914, 0), (172716, 'The inability to rise above one''s inherited ism and ideology makes one live and die a fool, just a folly.', 4618, 0), (172717, 'To live unhappily, is failing life.', 4618, 0), (172718, 'When you finally understand the meaning of life, you come to the conclusion it has none after all', 3682, 0), (172719, 'One the advantages about this life is that you can hate someone without knowing him', 23285, 0), (172720, 'Most of our waking life is make believe. If there was a way to record every dream that crosses our minds, the true nature of humans would be laid bare', 3682, 0), (172721, 'Do you know why we show respect to life when it shows none to us? Family is the answer', 3682, 0), (172722, 'You don''t need to play every ball but every ball needs your judgement.', 379, 0), (172723, 'Anything man can make, man can destroy.', 918, 0), (172724, 'What fun it would be," he thought, "if one didn''t have to think about happiness!', 1032, 0), (172725, 'We are the directors of our own life, creating our own version of truth, which can be humorous, pleasurable, miserable, brutal, or stupid. Reconciling loss and misfortune can provide a sense of sublimity or catharsis.', 2764, 0), (172726, 'We unthinkingly build the pilings of our lives upon whatever comes along. Like it or not, we play the hand that fate deals us. If fate is kind, some people credit their fortuitous circumstances to their ingenuity and resoluteness. If fate is cruel, some people curse God. The truth is that an unenlightened person resists suffering, they continually wish for a world different than it is, whereas an enlightened person learns how to suffer heroically.', 2764, 0), (172727, 'There is no such thing as bad people.we''re all just people who sometimes do bad things.', 316, 0), (172728, 'Enjoy the Journey!', 33, 0), (172729, 'I wish for sorrow to be a full stop and happiness to be a comma in my life.', 5761, 0), (172730, 'I''ve nothing against people. Just a***oles. But then, most people are.', 4618, 0), (172731, 'An examined life, an enigmatic investigation of reality, is required in order for a person to realize a transcendent spiritual journey. A contemplative soul is bound to live life more intensely than someone whom is concerned exclusively with living an external existence.', 2764, 0), (172732, 'On a supra human level, yeah, I got That Which Is. Yet on a simple human level, rare are times when either my left or my right foot is not in some kind of shit.', 4618, 0), (172733, 'Seeing Oneam undone!Enemy norlo! friend-sans One-is none.That! is "am"One-o-One!', 4618, 0), (172734, 'everything thing in life goes really really very very deep and ally you have to show the world is ,its just on the SURFACE', 31915, 0), (172735, 'We have started a journey since our birth and yet,we have to travel a lot.Just like a river keep flowing into the ocean because of its essence,we are an essence of time traveling with its wit and bit.', 15740, 0), (172736, 'Sometimes,just do what your mind tells you to do.Just don''t care about people.Because,neither you can afford loosing that time nor people will care after sometime.So just be who you are.', 15740, 0), (172737, 'Life is my greatest enemy.', 12725, 0), (172738, 'Strive through your adversities like a great football striker. Concentrate on the goal post and your ability to score a great goal. Let your attention be on your strength and your distinctive dexterity that can beat the strength and oppositions of your defenders and not the height, strength or boldness of the defenders.', 4606, 0), (172739, 'I know this feeling of being a ghost in your own life - no one sees you, no one feels you, so you stay still as if you could actually disappear at any moment.', 14688, 0), (172740, 'Time alone is the gift of self-entertainment - and that is the font of creativity', 1844, 0), (172741, 'Some wounds were worth bearing for the healing they brought.', 6452, 0), (172742, 'We were immortal, did you know that? Did you feel it like me? We had the world at our feet and we were going to live forever. Then came life – growing inside you – and I became mortal.', 6452, 0), (172743, 'Great books live longer than people.They are gonna bury us all.', 31916, 0), (172744, 'Humans, left to own misguided devices, scratches the Divine in the self as one would the lice, but remember to lick well all the vices.', 4618, 0), (172745, 'Sometimes, It''s awesome to be childish with your partner .Otherwise you are missing out.', 31917, 0), (172746, 'If a religion asks one to kill another just because he or she follows not this ism, nor agrees with it; then, it''s a hell-hole, worse than a prison. Run away, and far from it. As though your butt is on fire. And before you, yourself are imprisoned.', 4618, 0), (172747, 'Given the situation I had gotten myself into, I just chose the path that seemed most likely to succeed and did the best I could. But Shota died so suddenly. His death ripped open a deep fissure in my life. It was a cruel and heedless truth that I will never be able to comprehend. No matter what I do, I cannot change it. Is there any meaning in this world where Shota could die such an inexplicable death? That fissure spread through me unexpectedly. A responsible person would probably tell me to smile even though he’s gone. They’d probably say Shota, even though he was only a child, would have wanted me to lead a good life. But I don’t need to hear those words. This world is overflowing with hackneyed expressions like that. They can comfort most people, but they make me suffer. Words that most people nod along to make those who can’t nod along suffer. They alienate them. What about words that can reach someone like me? Do those exist? I am twisted. I can’t look at the world straight. But why am still trying to live on? Even though I think it would be better to curse the world, smile perversely and die.', 26714, 0), (172748, 'The hallway felt like time itself, and Patricia Buckingham and I were standing at opposite ends-her looking back on all she''d seen, me wondering what lay ahead.', 674, 0), (172749, 'I have it in my head that when we’re born, God writes things down on our hearts. See, on some people’s hearts he writes happy and on some people’s hearts he writes sad and on some people’s hearts he writes crazy and on some people’s hearts he writes genius and on some people’s hearts he writes angry and on some people’s hearts he writes winner and on some people’s hearts he writes loser.', 186, 0), (172750, 'Endeavour to appreciate life while you experience it, for some will never experience life again, because they are six feet inside the grave.', 5089, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (172751, 'Life is like a mirror.Cry and you see a crying face,Frown and you see a Sad Face !Smile and it smiles back at you !', 22576, 0), (172752, 'I slip away into the night, I won''t have much to take. Only the story of this life, with you, I leave behind', 31918, 0), (172753, 'I know it''s me that needs this moment. Your hand to hold my heart still cares. A thought I will hold when I wake in the morning, when I turn to you and you''re not there.', 31918, 0), (172754, 'Life is about making good choices, Matt. One after the other. They pile up day after day. It''s only when you look back that you can see what the choices led to. What you''re able to stand on.', 4260, 0), (172755, 'In the end it''s only words, my dear.', 31919, 0), (172756, 'I now view life as a complex and unpredictable affair that cannot be mastered. It can be embraced. It can be negotiated more or less skillfully. But mastered? Not a chance.', 31920, 0), (172757, 'However smart and determined you are, your life is always going to consist of light and darkness, joy and sadness, good or bad, up and down, yang and yin.', 31920, 0), (172758, 'If you can’t laugh at your life, then your life is a punchline in a bad joke.', 31921, 0), (172759, 'It is too simpleto pet a stray dogthen watch it run under a carand say it wasn''t mineIt is too simple to admire a rosethen pick it and forgetto put water in the vaseIt is too simple to use a personfor loving without lovethen leave him standing aloneand say I don''t know himanymoreIt is too simple to know one''s flawsthen live them at great cost to othersand say that''s just the way I amIt is too simple the way we sometimes live our livesfor after all life simply isa serious matter', 31922, 0), (172760, 'I''m willing to grind, endure & suffer to wake that beast within me, to grow, accomplish & win.', 4306, 0), (172761, 'You need only claim the events of your life to make yourself yours. When you truly possess all you have been and done, which may take some time, you are fierce with reality. When at last age has assembled you together, will it not be easy to let it all go, lived, balanced, over?', 12526, 0), (172762, 'I ask the nurse wrapping up her dispensing duties if I need any meds, and she says I''m not scheduled for any. I ask her if I can have some. She asks what I need them for. I tell her, to deal with this crazy place. She says if they had pills for that, they wouldn''t need places like this in the first place, would they?', 1186, 0), (172763, 'Let nothing put me to unease,nothing to deceive.I have conceived,I exist.Because I am blessed,To gather time,in hearing,my breath,so tranquil.To life,I am, thankful.', 2965, 0), (172764, 'What life means has individual answers for each of us.', 3548, 0), (172765, '...[T]here are days when emptiness is spacious, and non-existence elevating.', 12526, 0), (172766, 'I admire a contented mind. I revere enjoyment of the simple things. I can imagine that contentment has a high degree of truth. But the human tendency is to take good as normal, and one''s natural right, and so no cause for satisfaction and pleasure. This is accompanied by the habit of regarding bad as abnormal and a personal outrage.', 12526, 0), (172767, 'Some teachers only teach us and go but some teachers teach us and they leave indelible footprints which continue to teach us forever! Great teachers live and leave distinctive footprints. Great teachers, though they go, their footprints forever live in our minds and inspire the body and the soul in a distinctive way !', 4606, 0), (172768, 'Life is truly a miracle and must be protected, safeguarded and treasured.', 31923, 0), (172769, 'I am moving the rudder, shifting the course of my life. I have not thought of it this way before, but that is what I am doing. Taking my fate into my own hands, turning dreams into reality. And there is nothing more sacred or precious than that. To choose a direction: but how often do we miss the signposts?', 31924, 0), (172770, 'My best trip is yet to come.', 31925, 0), (172771, 'I say to life, "You are very hard", and I also say: "We are blind, we prefer to be blind. It is easier...". Life has to be hard to have any affect on us; even now we hardly notice it. Beyond that can one go? I must. I add, "We are also blind to the miracles of good that come to us. We hardly heed them, we even protest against them". Then I am left where I was, appalled by the hardness of life, knowing we are forced to be unwilling heroes. Suddenly I wonder--is all hardness justified because we are so slow in realizing that life was meant to be heroic? Greatness is required of us. That is life''s aim and justification, and we poor fools have for centuries been trying to make it convenient, manageable, pliant to our will. It is also peaceful and tender and funny and dull. Yes, all that.', 12526, 0), (172772, 'There are hundred reasons to worry but the only way to keep out of this ''net'' of worry is to pray.', 11739, 0), (172773, 'And remember, it truly is a great Life', 31926, 0), (172774, 'There are problems and there are problems. One big problem and a great paradox in the arena of life is the problem of where or how a person is now and where or how he wants to be tomorrow. Had it not been this problem, we would have been relaxing all day long', 4606, 0), (172775, 'We all make mistakes. The more you punish yourself for them, the harder it is to live.', 31927, 0), (172776, 'Your Life Doesn’t Need A Happily-Ever-After To Be A Damn Good Story', 31928, 0), (172777, 'and there were times when i felt lost,but that did not stop me,for the further i went ,the more i collected myselfas i walked awayand the more i walked awaythe closer i got it to all,,,and in the end, i became the journey,and like all journeys,i did not end, i justchanged my directions.', 7504, 0), (172778, 'We must not just be recipients but givers! We must not just be keepers but donors! Giving brings relief and sharing enlightens the heart. Caring joins and showing love is life. It is never enough to acquire all acquisition. It is never enough to have all our ambitions. We must endeavor to give for giving out of a true heart is a true love and a true love is life.', 4606, 0), (172779, 'If you accept life as a competition you will never be completely happy but if you accept life as a journey you will always be happy', 31929, 0), (172780, 'I never settled with anything. It was like a pendulum; swinging back and forth but never reached a comatose state. As a sequence of events around me unfolded, I struggled to understand who I was, whose child I was and whether I would ever find a way home.', 20994, 0), (172781, 'Tomorrow is not a day. It''s an attitude. It''s a symbol of the human spirit''s desire to keep getting better. It''s that curious mind that asks ''what''s next''?Tomorrow is not ushered in by the cock''s crow. Tomorrow dawns when today is better than yesterday...when we create something new.', 11381, 0), (172782, 'You Can''t Live If You Can''t Die', 21022, 0), (172783, 'To strive to better oneself is natural and expected. To abandon oneself in an effort to attain a new self is foolish and unhealthy.', 3627, 0), (172784, 'There are a lot of human experiences that challenge the limits of our language.', 1305, 0), (172785, 'For the shadows to stop growing. For people to stop being angry.', 1305, 0), (172786, 'A Reader lives life (personal) within Life (social).', 31930, 0), (172787, 'Life is going to give you things that you deserve instead of what you plan or want. Always thank God for your profits and losses. Because God plans best for us.', 15113, 0), (172788, 'The paths you walk in life should always be by design, either consciously or subconsciously.', 11173, 0), (172789, 'Elevate yourself away from anything or anyone who stunts your growth by distraction, you will never get round to watering your own plant if you wait for there approval to do so. Before you know it there garden will be full and yours would never have been started.', 6378, 0), (172790, 'Live deep instead of fast.', 31931, 0), (172791, 'To dream is to allow our subconscious thoughts exceed our limitations', 31932, 0), (172792, 'People see stories everywhere," Regine says. "That''s what my father used to say. We take random events and we string them together in a pattern so we can comfort ourselves with a story, no matter how much it obviously isn''t true." She glances back at Seth. "We have to lie to ourselves to live. Otherwise, we''d go crazy.', 258, 0), (172793, 'Success is attached to mentality of a man''s maturity', 31933, 0), (172794, 'Death is the first and final entry in the book of this life.', 14710, 0), (172795, 'relations are the failures of life..', 31934, 0), (172796, 'Great struggles make for great stories.', 1864, 0), (172797, 'What goes into our mind matters a lot to the success or failure of our lives. For so many people, what they heard triggered their steps that led them into discarding the real value of their lives. For so many people, what they heard became a spring board that shot the real value of their lives to a glorious height and for so many people, what they heard made them to choose never to do anything in life. Until you lose your hearing, you shall always hear. But, what you hear and what you deduce from what you hear must not just be distinctive but sound enough to make you take a distinctive step which will produce a distinctive footprint. If you fail to mind the seed of what goes into your mind today, you shall surely mind the fruits of what went into your mind yesterday tomorrow. Mind your mind!', 4606, 0), (172798, 'The moment when your heart’s rhythm synchronises with the chants of the holy temple, you find God in your soul. It was noisy yet peaceful. They were all dancing in the packed hall, with eyes closed and hands swinging up in the air. It was as if the motto of life was nothing but to enjoy this very moment and taste the love of the almighty.', 23353, 0), (172799, 'I am obsessed with good buying books', 2878, 0), (172800, 'We never accept the unaccepted, that which makes us uncomfortable. We love to ignore things till they can no longer be ignored.', 23353, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (172801, 'Volume II, Chapter 4"How unwise had the wanderers been, who had deserted its shelter, entangled themselves in the web of society, and entered on what men of the world call "life,"—that labyrinth of evil, that scheme of mutual torture. To live, according to this sense of the word, we must not only observe and learn, we must also feel; we must not be mere spectators of action, we must act; we must not describe, but be subjects of description. Deep sorrow must have been the inmate of our bosoms; fraud must have lain in wait for us; the artful must have deceived us; sickening doubt and false hope must have chequered our days; hilarity and joy, that lap the soul in ecstasy, must at times have possessed us. Who that knows what "life" is, would pine for this feverish species of existence? I have lived. I have spent days and nights of festivity; I have joined in ambitious hopes, and exulted in victory: now,—shut the door on the world, and build high the wall that is to separate me from the troubled scene enacted within its precincts. Let us live for each other and for happiness; let us seek peace in our dear home, near the inland murmur of streams, and the gracious waving of trees, the beauteous vesture of earth, and sublime pageantry of the skies. Let us leave "life," that we may live.', 1161, 0), (172802, 'Let us make an endeavour to live life in such a way that it becomes an example in itself which others can follow', 20518, 0), (172803, 'This isn’t like a job we have while we go to college. This is what we like — feed ourselves with.', 31935, 0), (172804, 'Bankrupt"One midnight, deep in starlight still,I dreamed that I received this bill:(- - - - IN ACCOUNT WITH LIFE - - - -):Five thousand breathless dawns all new;Five thousand flowers fresh in dew;Five thousand sunsets wrapped in gold;One-million snow-flakes served ice-cold;Five quiet friends; one baby''s love;One white-mad sea with clouds above;One hundred music-haunted dreamsOf moon-drenched roads and hurrying streams;Of prophesying winds, and trees;Of silent stars and browsing bees;One June night in a fragrant wood;One heart that loved and understood.I wondered when I waked at day,How—how in God''s name—I could pay!', 31936, 0), (172805, 'See yourself as a long-term work in progress, not a short-term project of preservation.', 6304, 0), (172806, 'I did so want to hear a singer. I miss the sound of a woman''s voice, the way they look and smell.', 31937, 0), (172807, 'The ultimate way to change something is to change what is behind that something. Change what is behind something and something will change!', 4606, 0), (172808, 'Just because I''m young, that doesn''t mean I don''t have a point.', 31938, 0), (172809, 'Death is easy, living difficult.', 4618, 0), (172810, 'Even if things do not work out as you thought they should for you, they do - in their own way, as they were meant to.', 4618, 0), (172811, 'Learn to be comfortable in your own skin despite what you see and hear.', 31939, 0), (172812, 'While you’re hating your life just because you can’t get what you want, someone is praying to have a life like yours..!!', 29260, 0), (172813, 'Life is a long boring drive on an empty road punctuated by special moments that make the journey worth taking.', 9860, 0), (172814, 'It is better to remain silence than to speak rudely when being provoked.', 2878, 0), (172815, 'No house is big enough for the rule of two women.', 2557, 0), (172816, 'Every day is a good day. There is something to learn, care and celebrate.', 379, 0), (172817, 'Standing at the edge of timeAlmost falling down to the dark abyssAs I near the end of mineI reminisce the things I will missThe smiles and laughterRunning around without a careThe time when my grin will never falterBeing so free, willing my soul to bareHeartaches, heartbreaks and tearsNow I know better and to myself I will never lieBecause in woe, I learned to love and never fearThose were the best and worst moments of my lifeAs the memories rush back to meI look down and now I feel relievedBecause when it is timeEverything will be fine when I leave', 31940, 0), (172818, 'Time takes it all, whether you want it or not. Time takes it all, time bears it away, and in the end there is only darkness. Sometimes we find others in that darkness, and sometimes we lose them there again.', 578, 0), (172819, 'There are unlimited possibilities in life.', 2878, 0), (172820, 'Sometimes, we need to accept that life doesn’t always go the way we planned.', 12100, 0), (172821, 'Time is itself on time, are you', 14951, 0), (172822, 'Know! You don''t know!Don''t know! You know!', 31941, 0), (172823, 'The more you live, the more today you see, the more yesterday’s you left and the more tomorrow you say! Only those who have lived long can best tell the regrets of yesterday, the lessons in today and the real reasons to ponder before you say and think of tomorrow!', 4606, 0), (172824, 'The man died inside cannot live outside. ‪', 31942, 0), (172825, 'Hardwork and perseverance were the keyOne way ticket out of this hellThought I should make myself worthyOf the quest that lied aheaf', 31943, 0), (172826, 'It is only when we first do what we are SUPPOSED to do, that we set ourselves to be successful at what we WANT to do', 5546, 0), (172827, 'Insofar as there shall always be a desire, there shall always be a want and there shall always be a need', 4606, 0), (172828, 'Our whole life is wasted in trying to change others. For a change, try to change yourself! It is easier and at least under your control.', 11739, 0), (172829, 'In his last days on this earth, he’d wanted to know if this was all there was.', 6777, 0), (172830, 'You are given a life, a death. Understand both while living, and before dying. Or you''d have wasted a life, a death.', 4618, 0), (172831, 'Respect all people as you do your people, and you would be a fine people.', 4618, 0), (172832, 'Killing of an innocent, alike killing of humanity.', 14951, 0), (172833, 'Your destiny - by hook or crook, by this way or that, at some corner or nook - will catch up with you.', 4618, 0), (172834, 'You are the Winner,You are the Looser,You are the Sinner,It all depends upon how serious are you about.', 14951, 0), (172835, 'Sometimes I return back to the state of mind I had as a child when I believed nothing was impossible.', 10046, 0), (172836, 'Life is beautiful. Suffering is due to unconscious following.', 379, 0), (172837, 'My first interview was with eighty-eight-year-old folk artist Marcia Muth… ‘Your life does change as you get older,’ she told me. ‘You get into what’s important and what’s not’.', 18374, 0), (172838, 'Fifty years from now, I will not be remembered for how much money I earned, the type of home I lived in or the car I drove, but on whether I made a difference to someone''s life.', 12100, 0), (172839, 'A great life evolves with gratitude.', 2878, 0), (172840, 'I''ve looked at life from both sides now From up and down and still somehowIt''s life''s illusions I recallI really don''t know life at all', 16696, 0), (172841, 'Life is like a box of chocolates: You get through what little actual good stuff there is right away, then you constantly fool yourself into believing there''s still something good in whatever''s left.', 3833, 0), (172842, 'The man who dies rich dies disgraced leaving the earth without making it better than he met it. Give to humanity.', 8450, 0), (172843, 'Life moves very fast. it rushes us from heaven to hell in a matter of seconds.', 34, 0), (172844, 'It''s a strange experience, dying. People talk about how it creeps over you like a warm blanket. That''s not true. It starts out warm, but then it hits you like a bucket of icy water after stepping out of a sweat lodge. Then it''s all black like a void. I would know. I died and lived to tell about it.', 31944, 0), (172845, 'All I want in my life is-My mind to Think and My body to Run.', 21285, 0), (172846, 'God''s silence is an answer itself.', 19133, 0), (172847, 'life is the most valuble thing money isn´t', 31945, 0), (172848, 'Living for oneself, respecting our being is one of the most important code of anybody''s existence and a person who fails to justify his being fails to justify the society as well..', 15083, 0), (172849, 'If only you can add just one great and distinctive thing to your life each day, you shall surely not just live and leave one great thing!', 4606, 0), (172850, 'Keep a vigil on those who push you down always and leave them alone. Stay away from them so that you don''t waste your precious time refuting them, trying to impress them or proving your point to them. Let them not occupy any free space in your mind.', 11739, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (172851, 'Do you ever feel like you''ve been waiting your entire life for a specific moment when it''ll all make sense?', 31946, 0), (172852, '...What is easier for us isn''t necessarily what is better for us.', 22992, 0), (172853, 'When the situation demands action, know the end of the action before you start the action', 4606, 0), (172854, 'Every book is a safe heaven, many people don''t see it but I do.I see my chance to escape and be safe, I see the choice to stop or jump over the yelling, I see the key to help me get a better person.I see not different worlds, no, I see my universe.', 31947, 0), (172855, 'I''d tell them that it gets better. That they may not be able to beat death when their time comes, but they can beat death in life. I know it may not be an easy thing to do, but with the right person by their side they can conquer anything.', 23337, 0), (172856, 'A closed heart opens no mind.', 4618, 0), (172857, 'We don''t seek anyone out. We just wait and hope that people who want the same things come along.', 31948, 0), (172858, 'Your life can end at any time, and it can end more than once. But it can also begin more than once.', 9446, 0), (172859, 'Only those with tenacity can march forward in March', 4606, 0), (172860, 'Any situation is new adventure. Tighten your seat belt and enjoy the ride of life.', 2878, 0), (172861, 'The world is an arena where things represents things. It is a stage where the same thing is seen from different lenses as a different thing.', 4606, 0), (172862, 'Life itself will protect you. You will graduate to living a better life than you have ever lived till now! Your treatment and patience has paid off! You are life''s own student and have seen life from all the angles. You have come full circle and now it is time to rejoice. Say you are absolutely fine and it will be granted to you!', 11739, 0), (172863, 'Difficult times are ways to know and understand yourself and others in a better way. (From ''Voyage to Happiness'')', 11739, 0), (172864, 'I am happy to have love in my heart.', 2878, 0), (172865, 'It would be a remarkable life, if we live it in the same manner as we do once we find out we do not have much to live', 21049, 0), (172866, 'Five years back, I dreamed of me being what I am today.Five years later, I dream of me being what I am in future.Now, is the true version of me between my history and mystery....', 31949, 0), (172867, 'I think we''re supposed to know everything we can figure out. I don''t think we''re supposed to make up answers just because we can''t stand living with unanswered questions.', 31950, 0), (172868, 'The opinions of souls are their state of being.', 2878, 0), (172869, 'Outsource your anxieties to God. This ''outsourcing'' will help you in such a way that you will become only a witness to adverse situations, without becoming a part of the problem yourself.', 11739, 0), (172870, 'Think of a new day and think of a new purpose. Think of a new reason out of the reasons of yesterday. Think of the distinctive step that is worth taking to continue the footprints of yesterday. Each day comes with its own ideas. Each day comes with its own troubles. Each day comes with its own possibles and impossibles. What makes each day good or bad is not just our thoughts but, the steps we take which is influenced by our thoughts to obtain what is good or bad. Think of a new day; think of a distinctive footprint', 4606, 0), (172871, 'I mean that success has come early. And that is dangerous. Always dangerous.', 94, 0), (172872, 'I go towards him and put my hands on his face and I kiss him. “What do you feel, Holden?”He looks into my eyes. “You,” he says. “I feel you.', 29011, 0), (172873, 'Without doubt, it is a delightful harmony when doing and saying go together.', 663, 0), (172874, 'The dreams we had of finding meaning and fulfillment through our jobs have faded into the reality of professional politics, burnout, boredom and intense competition.', 23089, 0), (172875, 'Here now in his triumph where all things falter, Stretched out on the spoils that his own hand spread,As a god self-slain on his own strange altar, Death lies dead.', 7814, 0), (172876, 'Even everything will come to failure and seems it always like that, i’ll just start again. The biggest ability i have, is ability to keep repeat on fail.', 31951, 0), (172877, 'The bones of the oak tree that had stood by the spring branch during my youth were scattered about the ground, pieces of the skeleton of a majestic life that had passed while I was off growing up and old.', 11107, 0), (172878, 'We all spend our lives living beside the people we could have been.', 31952, 0), (172879, 'Baby is baby.', 2878, 0), (172880, 'There is always a method in the seeming chaos of creation” - The Monk', 12696, 0), (172881, 'There is no great path to greatness than true service. He who knows how to serve from a true heart and spirit knows what it takes to be truly great', 4606, 0), (172882, 'We have indeed, felt the effects of the epic journey that has been our life. We have covered a lot of ground, parenting, marriage, career, family and otherwise, and at times, surely, have felt the worse for the wear, especially when different circumstances have chewed us up and spit us out! When it felt as if the kiln was stoked to maximum heat levels, and that we would shatter into a billion pieces that would never all be found! There are some differences now, having a little more seasoning to us. First of all, now we understand there is no such thing as being finished. There is always more firing, refining and glazing we can experience, and it is only a matter of when and how, not if we will do so. Secondly, we look forward to it, knowing now it would take more heat than possible to break us beyond repair.', 14840, 0), (172883, 'Behind all the falling rain, the sun still hangs in the sky. And if the sun can hang in there through the rain, surely you can, too.', 31693, 0), (172884, 'I don''t want to die while I still have beautiful reasons to die for.', 3653, 0), (172885, 'What a shame. One loses so much when one can''t forgive.', 31953, 0), (172886, 'Simplicity allows a measure of freedom which the complexities of modern life greedily consume – freedom to think, to reflect, to create, to serve and be sincerely generous with our time and presence.', 25312, 0), (172887, 'You are the ocean, let the rivers come to you. You are the flower, let the bees come to you.', 379, 0), (172888, 'Isn''t it ironic that a nightmare can masquerade as a dream?', 5043, 0), (172889, 'It takes all of our life to learn how to live, and – something that may surprise you more – it takes just as long to learn how to die.', 1379, 0), (172890, 'I have lived, I have traveled the world, and now, like a worn-out clock, my life is winding down, the hands slowing, stepping out of the flow of time. If one steps out of time what does one have? Why, the past of course, gradually being worn away by the years as a pebble halted on a riverbed is eroded by the passage of water.', 24835, 0), (172891, 'It should be considered right to live and enjoy living. To be well, happy, and to express freedom, is to be in accord with Divine Law and Wisdom.', 5203, 0), (172892, 'Don''t try to preserve your energy. Rather, think of a worthwhile purpose in life and burn yourself up.... for that''s what is satisfying and fulfilling.', 5073, 0), (172893, 'A lie is still a lieeven if it’s disguisedas the truth.', 31954, 0), (172894, 'Fall down seven times, stand up eight.', 18020, 0), (172895, 'Stupidity is relatively harmless, but intelligent stupidity is highly dangerous', 378, 0), (172896, 'You see things You keep quiet about them. You understand.', 6, 0), (172897, 'everything is absurd.1 man spends his life earning money which he then saves even though he has no children 2 leave it 2. another puts all his efforts into becoming famous so that he''ll b remembered once dead, yet he doesn''t believe in a survival of the soul that would give him knowledge of that fame. yet another wears himself out looking 4 things he doesn''t even like.', 1114, 0), (172898, 'I keep my body in the best shape.', 2878, 0), (172899, 'That day, they learned that when there are two people, half the times they agreed and half the times they disagreed on every issue. What they were unwilling to accept is that they could get along very well together even if they disagreed half of the times.', 15136, 0), (172900, 'Nothing changes and everything does.', 31953, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (172901, 'Never expect too much from the life... it will only frustrate or disappoint you.', 30375, 0), (172902, 'Stay Alive in Your Own Life', 12522, 0), (172903, 'You were meant to be right here right now...so make the most of it!', 5043, 0), (172904, 'Our existence and our environment enclose entities of divinity.', 2878, 0), (172905, 'Giving someone gifts cannot equate to spending quality time with them. Never replace time with things. Time is precious and once lost cannot be regained. Make every moment count...you never know when your time will be up.', 3676, 0), (172906, 'The most important lesson we''d ever learn in life is that everyone is different and if we accept this for a fact and let them be, they can surprise us with what they can do and achieve.If others thought like us, acted like us and behaved like us, we''d all be xerox copies of each other and the monumental success we''ve achieved as a race (human race) would never have been possible.', 31955, 0), (172907, 'Life has a plan for each of us', 31956, 0), (172908, 'He that cannot cast off a possession has become the possessed', 31957, 0), (172909, 'Some memories just stay. They just refuse to give up on staying. Maybe it is good that they stay. It helps us stay rooted. It helps us to know who we really are.', 31958, 0), (172910, 'A new grace for a new life is what we need in the coming year.', 2878, 0), (172911, 'Is it as plainly in our living shown,By which way the wind hath blown?', 18951, 0), (172912, 'There was no burger so soggy that he would not eat it. No tequila so mean that he would not drink it. No car so covered with birdshit and rust that he would not drive it around town (and if it were a convertible, he''d have the top down, even in rain, even in snow). There was no flag he would not desecrate, no true believer he would not mock, no song he wouldn''t sign off-key, no dental appointment he wouldn''t break, no child he wouldn''t do tricks for, no old person he wouldn''t help in from the cold, no moon he wouldn''t lie under...', 105, 0), (172913, 'Life is What You Make it, The Choice is all Yours', 31959, 0), (172914, 'I have found that there is a difference in the type of action you take and the results that you receive. My definition of action that gets the results you desire – is relaxed inspired action- not desperate action or desperate reaction.', 26489, 0), (172915, 'And now she began muttering to herself. "God , who created you, must have known what He did. Enough is enough.', 16228, 0), (172916, 'If you wish to break with tradition, learn your craft well, and embrace adversity', 11124, 0), (172917, 'Control and manipulation are not love', 31960, 0), (172918, 'The nicest people I meet in life are those who work hard for everything they have', 31961, 0), (172919, 'Sometimes, until you do what you shouldn''t have done, you least remember what you should have done', 4606, 0), (172920, 'Be the good, kind, lovable person you want to see in the world. Every action counts and the more people who behave and act with love and caring the more the world becomes a better place. We can do this!', 16576, 0), (172921, 'Ashes don''t necessarily signify an end', 9702, 0), (172922, 'We got life to live, not to survive, do the things you always want to & be the person you always desire to be. don''t let other people deal with it..!!', 10372, 0), (172923, 'Life is so complicated that sometimes it is better to pass up.', 11143, 0), (172924, 'It''s not that we get all the answers in life. Its just that the questions disappear and there we flow with life - quenched yet thirsty', 31962, 0), (172925, 'Be youthful.', 2878, 0), (172926, 'Patient endurance is the greatest life survival skills.', 2878, 0), (172927, 'The people in our life is like the mountain and the river. Some people will stay as others will leave. Some will travel away and make their way back to you.', 30514, 0), (172928, 'Imagine life as ... black can become white, and white can become black. But white can remain if you show love and respect.', 22158, 0), (172929, 'Take a chance of your life, you''re risking nothing in this planet.', 30336, 0), (172930, 'Salvation Creek flows till date, endless tears of motherly love and manly regret.', 5414, 0), (172931, 'Once you learn how to diw, you learn how to live', 2128, 0), (172932, 'Once you learn how to die, you learn how to live', 2128, 0), (172933, 'False has many wings. Do not judge anything by its popularity.', 379, 0), (172934, 'I feel the reason we are all here, our purpose of being, is to help others find their little piece of happiness and heaven right here on earth...', 5043, 0), (172935, 'The Time (T) and Energy (E) we invest in others, people will take it and carry it with them.', 5043, 0), (172936, 'We can''t change yesterday, but we can change tomorrow...', 5043, 0), (172937, 'Be blind to people who mock at you,Be deaf to people who gossip behind you.', 5761, 0), (172938, 'You don''t have to be good all the times. It''s okay to be hurt sometimes. It''s okay to feel lost like you''re wandering around the dark. It''s the bad days that make the good ones so much better.', 14665, 0), (172939, 'As you begin to Awaken.. You discover yourself sitting in nature.. flowing like the river.. Trying to understand the purpose.. then realizing "Nature is Happening, that is its purpose".. You are just like the river flowing through nature.. Your purpose is to be like nature. Start Now.. in the precious moments.. for its the only time that exists.', 31963, 0), (172940, 'Man is born to live, not to prepare for life. Life itself, the phenomenon of life, the gift of life, is so breath-takingly serious!', 925, 0), (172941, 'Struggling isn''t a sign of failure but of strength. Keep pushing, keep striving...your best is yet to come!', 3676, 0), (172942, 'How is life a shaped? By parentage, siblings, calss and religion, by schooling, vocational choices, by friends, partnerships, children, by place and time, by illness and accident, and sometimes, but most rarely, by surprising choice.', 31964, 0), (172943, 'I don''t like laid back. I like action. This city has a constant desire to achieve. Just the way I also want to. My friends say that I have ambitions the size of the Himalayas but the desire to do so is the size of a pea. I don''t believe them. Someday they will change their opinions. Today is a starting point. I can feel it.', 31958, 0), (172944, 'If you don’t make your choices, others will choose for you.', 2878, 0), (172945, 'True enough. I say this all the time.Trez looked at his hands. “I didn’t ask for this.”“No one asks for life.” The executioner hiked iAm’s body up higher. “And sometimes they do not ask for death...', 108, 0), (172946, 'Nothing exists but my breath. I know this feeling. Usually it comes when something unexpected and momentously awful is about to happen, which doesn’t make sense now. I’m just going home.', 31965, 0), (172947, 'Daring life!', 2878, 0), (172948, 'To live life as anything less than love is not to live life at all.', 23399, 0), (172949, 'If you do not conquer self, you will be conquered by self.', 31966, 0), (172950, 'Life is a stampede to get to the top', 3682, 0);
